\zyb{Inspired by recent advancements in Reinforcement Learning with Verified Rewards (RLVR) and Group Relative Policy Optimization (GRPO), we propose \ours. Our framework comprises three key components: (1) a rule-based pipeline for high-quality training data construction; (2) a hierarchical reward function designed to capture multi-faceted feedback; and (3) a modified Dynamic Adaptive Policy Optimization (DAPO) algorithm for effective model fine-tuning. We initiate the process by employing multiple retrievers to collect diverse candidate evidence for each query.}
\zyb{Based on the retrieved results, we strategically balance the dataset by randomly assigning instances to either answerable or unanswerable categories. For answerable cases, we ensure the inclusion of ground-truth evidence, whereas for unanswerable ones, such evidence is intentionally withheld. This random assignment not only maintains a balanced distribution of solvability but also prevents the model from overfitting to specific retriever biases, thereby enhancing its generalization across diverse retrieval quality.}
During training, we adopt a small set of outcome-based reward signals rather than step-wise progress rewards. A format reward enforces a consistent output format, which in turn stabilizes downstream reward computation. A path selection reward guides the model to assess whether the retrieved evidence is sufficient and to choose appropriately between answering and abstaining. For answerable cases, a content accuracy reward encourages the model to identify and reference the essential evidence while producing a correct final answer.
Experimental results demonstrate that \ours~achieves state-of-the-art performance, outperforming significantly larger models and methods trained on more data. Remarkably, with only 2,000 annotated examples, our 4B-parameter model not only surpasses prior benchmarks in answer accuracy but also achieves a superior synergy between answer correctness and refusal reliability. This underscores the exceptional sample efficiency and robustness of \ours.

